<br>
    Easy way to test it nowadays.<br>
<br>
  Get a item focus effect for mana (since you say this glows on DoT spells, I would recomend Affliction Efficiency, as it is far more than 10 percent mana reduc).   Cast a spell on a mob, if BOTH ITEMS glow/shine, then it is not reducing your mana.<br>
<br>
   Cast a non harmful spell, see if it glows/shines.   If it shines for Complete heals, and not for Aego, then it is an aggro item IMO, because C-heal has huge aggro, and as far as I am aware, aego and other such buffs do not have aggro. <p><TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD>
